    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-22T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-22T07:00:00-05:00" n="299"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/8–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-22T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 22, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>464. My British colleague delivered a note against the present situation
                    yesterday evening to the Prime Minister, the Begents, the opposition leaders. I
                    assume that the Department has received text from British Embassy
                        Washington.<note n="43" xml:id="d299fn1">Text transmitted in telegram 8533,
                        A ugust 22, from London, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow as 237.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
